UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0378426686900269
AB  - The high degree of correlation between bank holding company (BHC) commercial paper ratings and the size of the issuing BHC raises a serious question about the raters' recognition of the international exposure confronting many of the large BHCs. Apparently the market realized this problem and as a result devised more detailed BHC rating categories. Recently the raters also responded by making widespread downgrades among the largest BHC commercial paper issuers.
